00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:44,700
I tell you everything, you know everything
about me, but I know nothing about you.

511
00:45:44,900 --> 00:45:47,100
Come on, I'm not a jealous guy.

512
00:45:47,300 --> 00:45:50,500
I'm superstitious.
- So not your department manager.

513
00:45:50,700 --> 00:45:51,700
The man of your heart.

514
00:45:53,500 --> 00:45:57,100
You don't confide in anybody.

515
00:45:57,900 --> 00:46:02,700
I'm hiding him, because it's serious.
I want to be sure he's for me.

516
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:04,900
Oh dear, a schoolgirl.

517
00:46:07,300 --> 00:46:08,600
But she did have guts.

518
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:12,700
She's really hiding him
because she was afraid of me.

519
00:46:12,900 --> 00:46:15,600
But I would never have
stolen her guy from her.

520
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,700
Besides, she was taking me for a ride.

521
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:19,500
Her big lesson about love
as the big enemy

522
00:46:20,200 --> 00:46:22,600
applied to others,
but not to herself.

523
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:42,700
Miss Sandrine Tessier?
- Yes.

524
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:46,700
I'm the secretary of Mr. Barnay Jr.
You're expected by the Board.

525
00:46:46,900 --> 00:46:49,100
Right now?
- Yes.

526
00:46:49,300 --> 00:46:50,800
I'll be right there.

527
00:47:05,300 --> 00:47:08,600
Nathalie?
I've hit the jackpot.

528
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:17,400
You didn't sleep with Barnay Jr., did you?
- No, they want to see me.

529
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:19,900
Keep your head cool.
Don't blow it.

530
00:47:20,100 --> 00:47:22,600
He tries to get girls
so he can hurt them later.

531
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:38,900
Come in.

532
00:47:51,300 --> 00:47:53,000
Damn, he's handsome.

533
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:57,000
For a moment I even forgot why I was there.
I came closer,

534
00:47:57,400 --> 00:48:01,300
not because I had to,
but to see him from up close.

535
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:04,500
And he turned out even more handsome.
- Sit down.

536
00:48:08,200 --> 00:48:10,600
Let me see the white raven.

537
00:48:11,300 --> 00:48:13,700
White raven?
- You, miss.

538
00:48:14,700 --> 00:48:16,400
What do you mean?

539
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:24,400
I'm going to give you an order.

540
00:48:24,600 --> 00:48:27,900
To become the second secretary
of Mr. Delacroix.

541
00:48:28,100 --> 00:48:31,600
Soon private secretary.

542
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:33,500
Don't speak. I'm ordering you.

543
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:37,400
And you can't leave the Barnay company.
- Why would I do that?

544
00:48:37,800 --> 00:48:40,500
In case you thought you didn't earn

545
00:48:40,700 --> 00:48:44,600
the job I'm ordering you to accept,
by your own work.

546
00:48:45,400 --> 00:48:49,300
Miss Tessier, the company can't do
without a precious element like you.

547
00:48:49,900 --> 00:48:51,300
A young woman

548
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:54,100
who gives her heart and soul
to work and overtime.

549
00:48:54,700 --> 00:48:57,300
Denies herself a personal life,

550
00:48:57,500 --> 00:48:59,700
hired for her arithmetic skills.

551
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:02,300
Although you're mainly a secretary.

552
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:04,800
You see, miss, these days...

553
00:49:05,600 --> 00:49:07,900
someone with your merit

554
00:49:08,100 --> 00:49:10,600
and morals

555
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:11,800
is a beautiful and rare find.

556
00:49:13,000 --> 00:49:14,900
One wonders why, by the way.

557
00:49:15,700 --> 00:49:18,500
We see the proof every day:
merit...

558
00:49:19,400 --> 00:49:20,800
that's the only thing that counts.

559
00:49:22,500 --> 00:49:23,600
I'm the living proof.

560
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:29,900
I congratulate you on your promotion.
See you soon, miss.

561
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:31,100
Your character intrigues me.

562
00:49:32,600 --> 00:49:35,700
My character?
- Your personality, I mean.

563
00:49:35,900 --> 00:49:37,900
Everybody really appreciates you.

564
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:43,700
Mr. Delacroix is a remarkable man.

565
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:46,400
And well positioned.
- What do you mean?

566
00:49:46,600 --> 00:49:50,500
That you're very interesting to...

567
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:52,900
the company and myself.
You can go now.

568
00:49:55,700 --> 00:49:58,500
Hello.
- Hello, Sandrine.

569
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:03,600
You look a bit pale.

570
00:50:04,400 --> 00:50:06,900
You haven't refused again, have you?

571
00:50:11,700 --> 00:50:15,100
Mrs. Mercier, please get a
bottle of champagne.

572
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:19,100
I announce to you the promotion
of Sandrine.

573
00:50:19,300 --> 00:50:21,300
She'll be my second secretary.

574
00:50:22,100 --> 00:50:26,400
You've served me with dedication for 15 years.
You deserve some help.

575
00:50:26,600 --> 00:50:30,200
But I can handle fine.
- Really, you'll be a lot happier.

576
00:50:34,300 --> 00:50:35,400
Sit down.

577
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:46,300
One month later, Nathalie had secured
her pre-pension.

578
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:27,000
Are you listening?

579
00:51:27,900 --> 00:51:29,400
Hello. Everything ok?

580
00:51:29,600 --> 00:51:32,100
I've got 2 tickets for Madonna tomorrow.

581
00:51:32,300 --> 00:51:34,900
That's not possible.
We're working until 10 o'clock at least.

582
00:51:35,100 --> 00:51:38,200
You do have time for a drink, don't you?
- Too much work.

583
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:41,600
Honestly, are you avoiding me?

584
00:51:41,800 --> 00:51:45,900
You haven't wanted to see me for weeks.
- I'm seeing you now.

585
00:51:46,100 --> 00:51:49,400
You know what I mean.
- I'm really busy.

586
00:51:56,900 --> 00:52:01,000
You know, soon we'll all be
completely lonely because

587
00:52:01,200 --> 00:52:03,900
of those machines, those computers.

588
00:52:04,800 --> 00:52:06,200
Sandrine?

589
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:18,900
Good evening, sir.

590
00:52:19,200 --> 00:52:20,800
There's nobody left.
Will you turn off the lights?

591
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:22,900
As always.
- Thank you, goodbye.

592
00:54:20,100 --> 00:54:21,200
Stop it.

593
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:32,200
Yes.

594
00:54:36,500 --> 00:54:37,900
One moment, please.

595
00:54:38,200 --> 00:54:39,500
The Japanese.

596
00:54:40,900 --> 00:54:44,500
Hello? Delacroix speaking.

597
00:54:47,500 --> 00:54:49,900
Yes, how are you?

598
00:54:50,100 --> 00:54:51,600
Fine, fine.

599
00:54:53,400 --> 00:54:55,700
Yes, the contracts will be ready.

600
00:54:56,100 --> 00:54:57,800
Within two months.

601
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:02,200
Stop it.

602
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:03,600
Don't do that.

603
00:55:04,200 --> 00:55:06,200
We're expecting you in Paris.

604
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:08,100
for the contracts.

605
00:55:14,700 --> 00:55:16,800
We're ready for the meeting.

606
00:55:17,000 --> 00:55:18,900
I'm coming.
Close the door.

607
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:34,000
I don't know

608
00:55:34,700 --> 00:55:36,500
what's happening with the line.

609
00:55:36,700 --> 00:55:38,400
I can't hear you.

610
00:55:39,300 --> 00:55:40,200
Can you hear me?

611
00:55:45,700 --> 00:55:46,600
I can't hear you.

612
00:55:52,100 --> 00:55:53,400
I'll call you back.

613
00:55:57,400 --> 00:55:59,700
Ok, I'll call you back.

614
00:56:02,900 --> 00:56:05,600
Everything ok?
- Yes, sure.

615
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:06,500
Where are you going?

616
00:56:19,700 --> 00:56:21,800
See you later then.
- Ok.

617
00:56:29,700 --> 00:56:32,900
Hi.
How is it going here?

618
00:56:33,900 --> 00:56:35,300
Fine.

619
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:37,800
There's something wrong with your tie.

620
00:56:39,700 --> 00:56:41,200
See you later.

621
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:45,800
Hello, Sandrine.

622
00:56:46,200 --> 00:56:47,900
Everything ok?
- And you?

623
00:56:48,100 --> 00:56:51,000
How are things with Delacroix?
- Fine.

624
00:56:51,500 --> 00:56:53,700
Will we see each other tonight?

625
00:56:55,400 --> 00:56:57,800
Yes, see you tonight.
- See you then.

626
00:57:06,700 --> 00:57:08,300
Miss...

627
00:57:09,500 --> 00:57:11,300
I need you right away.

628
00:57:51,300 --> 00:57:53,200
A shame I could never
afford that.

629
00:58:12,900 --> 00:58:14,600
Do you want to see my stockings?

630
00:58:23,400 --> 00:58:24,600
Stop it.

631
00:58:25,900 --> 00:58:27,600
You're crazy.

632
00:59:09,200 --> 00:59:10,300
Taxi!

633
00:59:33,000 --> 00:59:36,600
2 months ago I couldn't have known
you'd make me discover life...

634
00:59:37,500 --> 00:59:39,100
at the age of 50.

635
00:59:41,800 --> 00:59:45,300
Every second without you hurts.

636
00:59:45,500 --> 00:59:49,400
Please don't get attached to me.
- It's too late.

637
00:59:50,600 --> 00:59:52,700
It can't last between us...

638
00:59:53,900 --> 00:59:56,600
but I can't think of that
or I start to panic.

639
00:59:58,500 --> 01:00:00,800
The direct line.
Must be your wife.

640
01:00:05,500 --> 01:00:06,200
Hello?

641
01:00:07,400 --> 01:00:09,200
Oh, it's you.

642
01:00:10,100 --> 01:00:13,800
I must have given the loser
a short moment of happiness.

643
01:00:15,400 --> 01:00:16,800
He told me all these

644
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:20,300
sweet little things that showed
he's in love.

645
01:00:20,500 --> 01:00:24,300
I never experienced it myself.
I started to envy him for it.

646
01:00:24,500 --> 01:00:28,600
I pretended I loved him,
as if I came with him.

647
01:00:28,800 --> 01:00:33,200
Everything. And in the end
I had nothing at all.

648
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:36,300
Except Nathalie, but she was
no knight in shining armour.

649
01:00:36,900 --> 01:00:39,300
That's why I wanted Christophe.

650
01:00:41,500 --> 01:00:45,200
Do you know the Barnay family well?
- Especially the father.

651
01:00:49,600 --> 01:00:52,500
He's a self-made man,
old school.

652
01:00:52,700 --> 01:00:54,900
With a strong sense of honour

653
01:00:55,100 --> 01:00:58,300
and responsibility.
A dinosaur.

654
01:00:58,800 --> 01:01:03,100
We founded the company together
and overcame a lot of problems.

655
01:01:03,300 --> 01:01:05,800
That created a bond of mutual trust.

656
01:01:06,600 --> 01:01:09,900
I've often been invited to his chateau.
- Chateau?

657
01:01:11,100 --> 01:01:13,800
Can't you take me one day?

658
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:16,200
You know that's impossible.

659
01:01:18,500 --> 01:01:19,800
And Christophe?

660
01:01:20,100 --> 01:01:23,400
He got the most beautiful women
of the company.

661
01:01:23,700 --> 01:01:24,700
Tell me...

662
01:01:25,800 --> 01:01:29,100
Now that you're here, I'm jealous.
- Silly.

663
01:01:29,400 --> 01:01:33,600
No, really. I'm very afraid of him.
And of his father.

664
01:01:34,600 --> 01:01:38,700
He wants me to keep a discrete eye on him.
- Why?

665
01:01:39,100 --> 01:01:40,800
It goes back more than 20 years.

666
01:01:41,800 --> 01:01:45,200
The old man had to work hard
in his new company.

667
01:01:45,400 --> 01:01:47,900
One day he had to go to Africa
for 2 months.

668
01:01:48,900 --> 01:01:53,600
Little Christophe stayed with his mother
and his sister, who was a baby still.

669
01:01:53,900 --> 01:01:58,500
They had no staff yet, back then.
The mother died suddenly.

670
01:01:59,800 --> 01:02:02,000
A heart attack. Totally unexpected.

671
01:02:03,100 --> 01:02:07,200
Little Christophe was unshaken and
stayed with his dead mother

672
01:02:08,100 --> 01:02:11,100
for almost two weeks,
without telling anybody.

673
01:02:11,300 --> 01:02:13,600
Not even his father over the phone.

674
01:02:14,400 --> 01:02:16,900
The body started to decompose.

675
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:20,200
The boy only moved
to feed his little sister.

676
01:02:20,800 --> 01:02:22,000
How old was he?

677
01:02:22,300 --> 01:02:23,500
Nine.

678
01:02:24,300 --> 01:02:27,200
There were no consequences,
he was doing fine even.

679
01:02:28,700 --> 01:02:31,400
Except, he wasn't afraid
of anything or anybody anymore.

680
01:02:31,600 --> 01:02:34,600
He said: "We're just a piece of wood."

681
01:02:34,800 --> 01:02:37,700
He kept saying he wanted
to attack the sun,

682
01:02:37,900 --> 01:02:41,200
take it away from the earth
or set the world to fire with it.

683
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:44,200
he also said: "That would be criminal."

684
01:02:44,500 --> 01:02:48,400
Or "Would that make
me as evil as God?"

685
01:02:48,800 --> 01:02:50,200
Boy talk.

686
01:02:50,400 --> 01:02:53,800
Except he still said it when he was 19
and when he was 25.

687
01:02:54,600 --> 01:02:58,700
And he defied death,
in the air, with his car.

688
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:01,400
He manipulated people for fun

689
01:03:02,400 --> 01:03:06,300
and he hung out with dangerous types,
to see whether they would kill him.

690
01:03:07,100 --> 01:03:08,900
He pushed women to suicide.

691
01:03:09,100 --> 01:03:11,500
Gossip.
- No.

692
01:03:11,900 --> 01:03:14,200
He seduced a number of employees.

693
01:03:14,900 --> 01:03:18,200
They say he tortured
and hurt them to the point

694
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:20,700
that two of them poured petrol over themselves

695
01:03:21,300 --> 01:03:22,900
and set themselves on fire.

696
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:25,600
They buried alive in front of him.

697
01:03:26,300 --> 01:03:28,000
Do you think he's mad?

698
01:03:28,700 --> 01:03:30,600
He knows perfectly well what he's doing.

699
01:03:30,900 --> 01:03:33,300
It's the women who are crazy.

700
01:03:33,800 --> 01:03:37,700
Crazy about him. Especially if they know
about their predecessors.

701
01:03:38,800 --> 01:03:40,500
I wanted to fire him

702
01:03:40,800 --> 01:03:43,500
or at least put him out of action.
But that's impossible.

703
01:03:43,700 --> 01:03:48,000
His father feels so guilty
he forgives him for everything.

704
01:03:48,300 --> 01:03:52,300
Maybe, after his death, he'll give me
some control over his son.

705
01:03:52,500 --> 01:03:54,000
That would be good.

706
01:03:54,300 --> 01:03:57,200
Thanks to his relations,
Christophe's untouchable.

707
01:03:57,500 --> 01:04:01,200
If he had the power,
he'd be terrifying.

708
01:04:02,700 --> 01:04:05,400
I've been wanting to tell you for a while...

709
01:04:05,700 --> 01:04:08,500
Why don't you get a replacement
for Mrs. Mercier?

710
01:04:10,100 --> 01:04:12,400
But I'm constantly drowning in work.

711
01:04:12,700 --> 01:04:15,600
They'd be on to us soon
and they'd start gossiping.

712
01:04:15,900 --> 01:04:18,600
Not at all.
I have a friend who'd be suitable.

713
01:04:19,100 --> 01:04:20,400
Please don't insist.

714
01:05:27,000 --> 01:05:29,600
leave me alone.
Don't touch me.

715
01:05:35,100 --> 01:05:35,900
Give it.

716
01:05:39,500 --> 01:05:40,800
You didn't want to take the whole bottle, did you?

717
01:05:44,000 --> 01:05:45,500
What's wrong?

718
01:05:47,300 --> 01:05:50,100
Please... tell me.

719
01:05:51,400 --> 01:05:52,600
Come on.

720
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:07,600
You don't want to tell me?

721
01:06:10,300 --> 01:06:12,300
You should talk about it. It relieves.

722
01:06:15,000 --> 01:06:17,700
You act like a girl in love
who was rejected.

723
01:06:21,300 --> 01:06:23,600
Was it a man who wasn't available?

724
01:06:24,300 --> 01:06:25,800
We're all the same.

725
01:06:27,300 --> 01:06:28,900
You can't do anything for me.

726
01:06:30,000 --> 01:06:31,700
It's nothing anyway.

727
01:06:32,500 --> 01:06:33,900
I was just dreaming.

728
01:06:35,300 --> 01:06:37,000
It'll pass.

729
01:06:41,600 --> 01:06:43,600
All that counts...

730
01:06:45,200 --> 01:06:48,000
is that we pursue our plan.

731
01:06:48,700 --> 01:06:50,400
You've got Delacroix.

732
01:06:50,800 --> 01:06:54,300
Convince him to replace Mrs. Mercier
with me.

733
01:06:55,700 --> 01:06:57,800
But never forget my advice.

734
01:06:59,700 --> 01:07:02,700
Don't fall in love,
stick with comedy.

735
01:07:02,900 --> 01:07:04,400
That doesn't hurt as much.

736
01:08:05,200 --> 01:08:08,000
Yes?
- Mr. Delacroix? The personnel department.

737
01:08:08,300 --> 01:08:12,200
Miss Tessier reported in sick
and will be absent for at least a week.

738
01:08:12,500 --> 01:08:15,400
What's wrong with her?
- Stress from over fatigue.

739
01:10:23,400 --> 01:10:25,000
Mr. Delacroix?

740
01:10:27,900 --> 01:10:30,600
Mr. Delacroix,
the signatures please.

741
01:10:31,100 --> 01:10:32,800
Come back in an hour.

742
01:10:33,000 --> 01:10:36,000
It's urgent, sir.
- Please.

743
01:11:00,300 --> 01:11:01,500
Come in.

744
01:11:07,900 --> 01:11:09,700
I'd rather talk to you alone.

745
01:11:09,900 --> 01:11:12,900
Why?
Nathalie can hear everything.

746
01:11:21,900 --> 01:11:24,200
Are you in love with her?
- No.

747
01:11:26,500 --> 01:11:30,100
What then?
- We both felt like it.

748
01:11:30,700 --> 01:11:32,400
Isn't it the same with you?

749
01:11:33,300 --> 01:11:36,600
That was not the same.
- It was.

750
01:11:41,100 --> 01:11:42,500
Why did you do that to me?

751
01:11:45,600 --> 01:11:48,000
I didn't want to see you again,
but it's not possible.

752
01:11:50,800 --> 01:11:52,600
I wanted to kill you the other day.

753
01:11:54,100 --> 01:11:55,800
I was in such pain I wanted to strangle you.

754
01:11:56,700 --> 01:11:58,600
I'm not your daughter or your wife.

755
01:12:01,800 --> 01:12:03,200
But I am your slave.

756
01:12:07,800 --> 01:12:09,700
I'm in the office 13 hours a day.

757
01:12:10,100 --> 01:12:12,200
Most evenings I'm with you.

758
01:12:12,900 --> 01:12:15,600
And also on Saturdays and Sundays now.

759
01:12:17,200 --> 01:12:18,800
And I have to be beautiful.

760
01:12:20,700 --> 01:12:24,200
Beauty parlour, shopping,
the laundry on Saturdays.

761
01:12:25,000 --> 01:12:27,000
But you refuse to help me.

762
01:12:27,700 --> 01:12:29,500
Do you want me to leave my wife?

763
01:12:31,200 --> 01:12:34,100
Do you want us to live together?
- No.

764
01:12:35,100 --> 01:12:37,800
I only want a bit less work.

765
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:40,700
